</taxonomicName>
. Externally it is similar to the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1068,1302,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[975,1068,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by having of bluish-green ground colour, but differs by more developed wing pattern. Head, thorax and forewing bluish-green, tegulae bordered with blackish-brown. Wing pattern in the male with more expressed blackish elements; female almost has not blackish lines, looks more similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[613,738,1409,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[613,738,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subbasal field half-filled with blackish brown, outlined with whitish line; antemedial line blackish, thin, distinct; orbicular and reniform expressed as white spots, orbicular with black bottom spot; medial mark in costal area small; medial line blackish, diffused, connected with costal mark; postmedial line blackish, thin, diffused; subterminal line as row blackish dashes outlined with whitish; subapicalapical mark brown with blackish dashes; subtornal-tornal mark brown; terminal line as row of interrupted blackish streaks; cilia brown with pale bluish-green marks opposite veins. The hindwing are dull greyish-brown around terminal margin, pale yellowish-grey towards base and along anal margin, with slightly traceable discal spot and medial fascia. In females blackish transversal lines expressed by white bordering lines, except medial line, which is formed by diffused blackish scales; the hindwing darker than in male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="352" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,909,2006]" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,369,1731,1756]" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[383,467,1731,1756]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 – 40" captionStartId="22.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1800]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 38 – 40. Belciana spp., male genitalia. 38. B. bicolor, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4177 (ZSM); 39. B. hemodi, Laos, slide GB 7412 (GB); 40. B. pinratanai sp. n., paratype, Thailand, slide MJP 707 (MJP). Most distinctive characters are marked by lines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241480/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[435,467,1731,1755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
). In the male genitalia it differs from other groups by extended flattened shape of valva and structure of the aedeagus with extended branches of carina armed with strong spines. Uncus more solid than in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,277,1802,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[151,277,1802,1827]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, less curved and more extended apically; valva broader more rounded and more sclerotised, sacculus more formed compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[484,609,1838,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[484,609,1838,1863]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">B. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with large basal coremata; harpe short, but broadly extended, flattened, terminated by small spine. Aedeagus with broad lobes of carina, vesica in joining with carina armed with row of strong short spines and cluster of spines; basal diverticulum with 
<number box="[883,953,1910,1934]" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14</number>
moderate and small cornuti.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,909,2006]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,151,355]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="352" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,1945,1970]" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[414,500,1945,1970]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 52" captionStartId="24.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,193,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 52. Belciana spp., female genitalia. 46. B. sp., Indonesia, Lombok I., slide GB 7362 (GB); 47. B. pratti, Papua New Guinea, slide GB 7700 (GB); 48. B. prasina, Sumatra, slide GB 7708 (GB). 49. B. bicolor, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4227 (ZSM); 50. B. hemodi, Laos, slide GB 12169 (GB); 51. B. sp., China, Shaanxi, slide RL 10996 (GR); 52. B. pinratanai sp. n., holotype, Thailand, slide GB 12177 (AB / ZSM); 53. B. scorpio, Thailand, slide GB 8252 (GB). Most distinctive characters are marked by lines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241482/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[468,500,1945,1970]" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" value="50.0">50</number>
</figureCitation>
). In the female genitalia antevaginal plate one-piece, like in 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1283,1945,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis">
<emphasis box="[1190,1283,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, much smaller than in 
<taxonomicName box="[332,418,1982,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasina">
<emphasis box="[332,418,1982,2005]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="351">prasina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. Ovipositor quadrangular; apophyses anteriores and posteriors ones moderate and equal in length, rather strong; antrum quadrangular, with not split antevaginal plate; ductus bursae short, membranous; corpus bursae elongated, with strongly sclerotised slightly ribbed patch in junction with ductus bursae and prominent lateral extension.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
